  "doc_id": "40243",
  "text": "UNAIDS has called for a major paradigm shift to a 'mission mode' in order to 'end AIDS' by 2030. They claim that the next five years will be critical if the ambition is to be achieved. Many of the changes they call for require a widespread uptake and adoption of new social practices -from policy makers, government employees and communities. However, the 'discourse' that surrounds the notion of what is precisely entailed in a change process such as the adoption of a new 'social practice' is contested [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
